The paper discusses the use of public key infrastructure (PKI) for securing vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs), which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a dynamic key distribution protocol, which involves network infrastructure and communication technologies, making it relevant to information theory (cs.IT), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and software engineering (cs.SE).
